ater \nUWA \nWanneroo \nWests Scarborough\n\n'''Other Perth Grades'''\n\nARKS  \nMandurah \nSwan Suburbs \nRockingham \nSouthern Lions \nBunbury\nPerth Irish Rugby \n\n'''South West Competition'''\n\nCollie \nDunsborough\nLeeuwin-Margaret River\n\n'''Great Southern Competition'''\n\nAlbany\nDenmark\nDryandra-Narrogin\nKatanning\nMount Barker\n\n'''Eastern Goldfields Competition'''\n\nBoulder\nBushwackers\nKambalda\nStormers\nWA School of Mines\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Western Australia|Sports}}\n*[[Perth Spirit]]\n*[[Western Force]]\n*[[Rugby union in Western Australia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|https://www.rugbywa.asn.au/}}\n* [https://www.westernforce.com.au/ Official website of the Western Force]\n* [http://www.twf.com.au/ TWF \u2013 Unofficial WA Rugby Website]\n\n{{Western Force}}\n{{Rugby union in Australia}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Australian rugby union governing bodies]]\n[[Category:Rugby union in Western Australia]]\n[[Category:Sports governing bodies in Western Australia]]\n[[Category:1893 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 1893]]\n", "text_old": "{{No footnotes|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox sport governing body\n|name             = Western Australia Rugby Union\n|abbrev           = RugbyWA\n|logo             = \n|logosize         = 150px\n|sport            = [[Rugby union]]\n|category         = \n|image            = \n|caption          = \n|jurisdiction     = [[Western Australia]]\n|founded          = {{start date and age|df=y|1893||}}\n|aff              = \n|affdate          = \n|region           = \n|regionyear       = \n|headquarters     = \n|location         = \n|president        = \n|chairman         = \n|chairperson      = \n|chair            = \n|chiefexec        = \n|vicepresident    = \n|director         = \n|secretary        = \n|coach            = \n|womenscoach      = \n|key staff        = \n|operating income = \n|sponsor          = \n|year closed      = \n|replaced         = \n|prevfounded      = \n|url              = https://wa.rugby/\n|countryflag      = \n|countryflag2     = \n|countryflag3     = \n|more             = \n|membership       = }}\n\nThe '''Western Australia Rugby Union (RugbyWA)''' is the [[Sports governing body|governing body]] of [[rugby union]] in [[Western Australia]], it was founded in 1893 and the inaugural 4 team competition commenced in 1895 with the I Zingari, Fremantle, Swans and Midland Junction Club's taking part. The WARU Senior Grade competition was contested from 1895 to 1913.\n\nThe Rugby Football code went into recess in the west from the 1914 season until 1928 when 4 Clubs; Wanderers, Rangers, Wallabies and Fremantle revived the First Grade Club Competition.\n\nIn 2004, RugbyWA successfully secured the fourth Australian Super 12 licence, entering a team in the expanded [[Super Rugby|Super 14]] competition from 2006, called the [[Western Force]]. RugbyWA has also established a series of development programs. The development team is the Perth Spirit, which has competed in the [[Australian Rugby Championship]] in 2007 and the [[National Rugby Championship]] since 2014.\n\nThere are currently 10 RugbyWA Board Members, President, D G Redpath who was re-elected in March 2012. Dr R J Perry is the current Chairman and Mr Arthur Hill is the current Patron.\n\nThe RugbyWA is a not-for-profit organisation run by its shareholding organisations \u2013 WA clubs and affiliated bodies (juniors, schools, referees, women's and country rugby). RugbyWA incorporates both Professional and Community Rugby. There is no private ownership of RugbyWA with profit generated re-invested into the game at all levels in Western Australia.\n\n=={{anchor|premier}}Premier Grade==\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox rugby league cup\n| title          = Fortescue Premier Grade\n| current_season = <!--leave blank-->\n| logo           = \n| logo_caption   = Fortescue Premier Grade Logo\n| pixels         = 300px\n| caption        = \n| sport          = [[Rugby union]]\n| founded        = {{start date and age|df=y|1928||}}\n| inaugural      = \n| folded         = \n| teams          = 14\n| country        = {{flagcountry|Western Australia}}\n| champion       = Cottesloe\n| season         = 2019\n| most_champs    = [[File:600px Giallo e Blu orizzontale con striscia bianca.png|20px|border]] [[Nedlands Rugby Union Football Club|Nedlands]] <small>(15 titles)</small>\n| website        = https://wa.rugby/competitions/comp?id=2GY4X4DfagBFcN3oz\n| ceo            = \n| TV             = \n| related_comps  = \n}}\n{{Main|Western Australia Premier Rugby}}\nThe Premier Grade is the highest level of [[Western Australia]] domestic club rugby union competition, contested annually from early April to mid August. It is managed by the [[Western Australia Rugby Union]] (RugbyWA), the FMG Premier Grade was named for lead sponsor Fortescue Metals.\n\n=== Premiers (since 1963) ===\n{{col-float|firstcol=16em}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! style=\"padding:0 2.5em\"|Champion\n|-\n|2019\n|[[File:600px Azzurro e Blu con striscia celeste.png|20px|border]] [[Cottesloe Rugby Union Football Club|Cottesloe]]\n|-\n|2018\n|[[File:600px upper Yellow HEX-FFE71E lower Green HEX-5E9A4D.svg|20px|border]] [[Associates Rugby Union Football Club|Associates]]\n|-\n|2017\n|[[File:600px Giallo oro e Rosso porpora con striscia bianca al centro.png|20px|border]] [[Wests Scarborough Rugby Union Football Club|Wests-Scarborough]]\n|-\n|2016\n|[[File:600px Giallo oro e Rosso porpora con striscia bianca al centro.png|20px|border]] [[Wests Scarborough Rugby Union Football Club|Wests-Scarborough]]\n|-\n|2015\n|[[File:600px Giallo e Blu orizzontale con striscia bianca.png|20px|border]] [[Nedlands Rugby Union Football Club|Nedlands]]\n|-\n|2014\n|[[File:600px upper Yellow HEX-FFE71E lower Green HEX-5E9A4D.svg|20px|border]] [[University of Western Australia Rugby Union Fo